reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 26, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Nicely priced fan, used it to replace the cpu heatsink fan that died. Doesn’t vibrate and works well so far, I liked the all black color and the sticker.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 10, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars SickleFlow 120 V2 RGB - The version 2 fans are fantastic!!
reviews.reviewText: **EDIT** 18 Months later and the first set as shown in the photos are still going strong, quiet, and bright. Actually back to buy a few more for another build. I also used their ARGB fans.. equally as good.Got introduced to the SickleFlow v2 fans when I bought their also recently released version 2 240mm aio. The fans are super quiet and the RGB is nice and bright. I was not planning on doing the whole case with them, but I was so impressed that i bought 4 more to replace my intakes and rear gpu radiator fan. At $14 a fan.. I am extremely impressed!! I even bought an extra to keep on the shelf. Why not at that price point.They are super quiet and even at 1800rpm, of course they will make some noise, but its not irritating like the EVGA fans I just took out. These are waaaay better. They also have rubber on the corners where you screw them in to help eliminate vibrations.The fans RGB connections are also setup that you can daisy chain them if they are in close proximity and then have a single RGB run to your header on the MB or a controller. Nice touch!The cables are also braided.. these do not look, feel, or function like $14 fans. I will be putting these in my future builds! As you can see, nothing but good things to say. I will be back if I run into issues with them over prolonged use.Case is a Cooler Master NR400 w/ ODD... guess I am team Cooler Master now. Wasn't planning on that, but the quality at their prices is unbeatable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 7, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Bought as the second fan on a CM EVO V2 cooler that used this fan
reviews.reviewText: I've been using Cooler Master 212 and later EVO coolers for years. I realize they aren't strong enough for real gaming systems, but for my needs they work wonderfully well. I don't really need a second cooler, but I like knowing that if one conks out I have some redundancy. And while I'm on the subject, the new V2 version of the cooler, though at $45 is long gone from the always-on-sale-for-$20-$25 days of a few years ago, is a delight to install, sooooooo much easier than the old model, both in terms of getting it right and not needing a 3rd hand.I bought this fan just because it matches the one that comes with the cooler. When I built my previous system (10 years ago) Cooler Master was selling 120mm "Excalibur" fans and I loved them. I used them for everything, as they moved a lot of air (if run at 100%) with reasonable noise, and still moved a lot of air if you turned them down (I used them in 3-wire mode) just a bit, and over the 10 years my old sysytem has been running with 7 of them, I just recently replaced one of them. I'm sorry they stopped making them but I seem to have been the only person who liked them.Anyway, for $10 for the black version of this fan, it seems like a good deal to me. They work well, move a nice amount of air (when required, they are being used as PWM CPU cooler fans) and I expect them to hold up well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Very good as replacement for Hyper 212 fan!
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I got a Hyper 212 RGB Black Edition. I liked it, but the fan was beginning to act up and make weird noises. Since the Hyper 212's default fan is actually an obsolete model that is no longer produced, I got the 4-pin RGB version of this instead. It performed noticeably better on my 5800X - about a 2 degrees C drop - while being significantly quieter. In addition, the frosted LED effect complimented my Trident Z RAM very well. I liked it so much I got another and used it to replace the stock exhaust fan that came with my case.Only docking 1 star because the price has since gone way up, and it isn't necessarily worth it unless they're $12 or less. At the time I got the fans, they were $8 each after a rebate was applied, which is a very good price for these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 23, 2023
Reviewed in the United States on April 8, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars just what I needed
reviews.reviewText: I have the cooler master hyper 212 black edition cooler for my CPU (Ryzen 9 5900x) and wanted a push/pull instead of just the one fan the hyper 212 came with. Went on Amazon, found this cooler master SickleFlow fan to do my push/pull and it works perfectly. The hyper 212 comes with a splitter for the CPU power socket on the motherboard so I was able to plug my SickleFlow into the splitter alongside the hyper 212 fan and it works great. The hyper 212 also comes with mounting gear that allows for you to install another fan as I did, so this worked out great for me. The RGB cords on these 2 fans daisy chain off of each other too because the SickleFlow has a splitter on its RGB cord that allows for you to daisy chain with another fan while you can plug the other side of the cord into an RGB socket on your motherboard. I do not plan on overclocking this CPU so that is why I went ahead and did this, so I can maximize the best possible airflow for it. Highly recommend you buy this fan if you are doing what I am doing. Great little setup and a good price too. Remember though, this is an RGB fan and not an ARGB. For those of you who do not know what that means it just means you cannot adjust the individual LED bulbs on this fan. All of the LEDs are the same color as one another.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Excelente precio para estos ventiladores!
reviews.reviewText: Reconozco que no son de los mejores ventiladores y los más silenciosos pero realmente que son buenos, armé mi PC Gamer ayer y las temperaturas mantienen excelentes incluso estando al 100% mis componentes, los ventiladores no se oyen en lo absoluto y teniendo el pc al lado de mi oreja, si sacan bastante aire caliente cuando coloco la mano en la parte superior, aún me falta cambiar el disipador y colocar otro ventilador en la parte inferior, hasta ahora van excelentes los que tengo y mantiene mis componentes frescos.
No hace mucho ruido, se configuro rápido con Aura Creator, y se sincronizo rápido con todo lo demás componentes. Fuera de eso es absurdamente fácil de instalar y funciona muy bien.

reviews.reviewTitle: Comes With 4 pin connector motherboard connector
reviews.reviewText: Perfect for case fan as well as replacement for cpu cooler, Comes With 4 pin connector motherboard connector control speed from biosAlso rubber padding at edges help dampened the sound.

reviews.reviewTitle: RGB works with Asrock Polychrome sync
reviews.reviewText: Got the RGB version and it is as described this isn’t a fixed RGB it works via a 4 pin PWM for power + 4 pin RGB to your motherboard CPU LED header (not ARGB) and synced up with my Asrock software without issue. It also comes with a 4 pin adaptor and plastic cover to daisy chain other fans up to LED. A little loud at 100% but not unbearable, perform average for a fan this size and LED is bright enough. Has rubber shock absorbers on each corner. The cables aren’t long around 30 cm suitable for smaller case builds. Would buy again

reviews.reviewTitle: Great case fan with vibrant RGB.
reviews.reviewText: I have this mounted in my Fractal Design Node 804 and it does a good job at exhausting the hot air out the back while looking great too. Its RGB is bright and vibrant and works well with the Gigabyte B450 AORUS M motherboard. At full speed it really does blow quite a lot of air, and of course its quite audible too. On medium to low speeds, it is pleasantly quiet. Not exactly silent, but quiet enough to be ignored easily.Installation is very easy and it comes in a nice packaging from Cooler Master.Overall, this is a nice case fan with good value.
